<TITLE> Three UGC members resign under 'pressure' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 1 (bdnews24.com) - Three members of the University Grants Commission have resigned, officials said Wednesday. One member submitted his resignation Tuesday while the rest Wednesday because of the pressure from the government. The steps came after education secretary Momtazul Islam asked four members of the five-member regulatory body to quit. Professor Faisul Islam Faruki quit Tuesday while Professor Mahbubullah and Professor Sultan Hossain Khan resigned their posts Wednesday. The fourth member, Professor Tareque Shamsur Rehman, may quit Thursday, one of his outgoing colleagues said. Rehman could not be reached for comment. Professor Mahbubullah told bdnews24.com that they had met education adviser Ayub Quadri before filing their resignations. He said they got to know from the adviser that the government had taken the decision as part of an ongoing reform to the education sector. UGC chairman Professor Nazrul Islam could not be reached for comment. bdn
